The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as image recognition and classification, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel learning framework using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of semantic information to improve recognition performance, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper uses benchmark datasets to evaluate the proposed method, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
